title: For Sale:  Thunder Beast Arms Corp MODEL 338BA SUPPRESSOR
postcontent:
YOU CAN BUY THIS HERE>Thunder Beast Arms Corp MODEL 338BA SUPPRESSOR

The 338BA is our high-performance .338 caliber suppressor design for applications where the rifle will be shot with and without the suppressor and recoil reduction is required in both cases. The 338BA effectively suppresses the extreme muzzle blast of the .338 magnums down to levels similar to suppressed .308. The 338BA brake is left attached to the rifle at all times, and reduces recoil when the suppressor is not used. When the 338BA suppressor is mounted to the brake, the rifle's "suppressed zero" returns and the mount design ensures accuracy.

We developed the 30BA and 338BA to meet the requirement that some customers have for a suppressor that mounts over a muzzle device. We haven't found a "quick mount" on the market that meets our accuracy and repeatability requirements, so we developed the BA series to mount over our brake and provide the same repeatability as our direct thread attach suppressors, like the 30P-1. The 30BA features a conical shoulder for rock solid POI repeatability and to make sure it never comes loose.

The 338BA, like the 338P-1, has additional volume to handle the gas pressure of the .338 Lapua Magnum, but only weighs fractionally more than a .308 suppressor.

The 338BA is constructed of titanium with a fully-welded baffle core. This material and method of construction provides a great strength to weight ratio. Our suppressors are designed from the ground up for superior accuracy. The 338BA can take whatever your big-bore precision rifle can dish out while keeping all your rounds on target.

The 30BA brake will accept the 338BA suppressor, so with a .30 caliber brake on your .308 and a .338 brake on your .338 Lapua Magnum, you can use a single 338BA suppressor on both. The 30BA suppressor will not fit on a 338BA brake.

title: For Sale:  JRC Just Right Carbine - SHOOTS GLOCK .45ACP MAGS 21 / 30
postcontent:
If you own a Glock Model 21 or Glock Model 30 in .45 ACP, then you may have special interest in this AR Style Rifle.  This carbine is made by Just Right Carbine and setup to take the Glock Magazines.  This particular rifle is setup for the caliber .45 ACP but you can purchase kits from Just Right Carbine that would convert the rifle to Glock 9mm magazines or Glock .40 S&W magazines.  Gun is several years old but in like new condition.  It has spent most of it's time a hard case in the trunk of my car. :)  Goes super with my Glocks that are in my car on or me.

Photo with White Background is most recent photos.  Sorry the Glock 30s is not included.  One Glock model 21 Magazine is included.  Photo with Red Background is an older photo that was taken and has some accessories shown on the gun that are not included in this sale.  Reflex Sight has been sold.  Flashlight has been moved to my Shotgun.

Just Right Carbine has a few glitches with the .45 caliber when they first started up until Just Right Carbine engineers tinkered (engineered) a few components to get the right balance with bolt speed, spring pressure, length of buffer tube, ect.  This carbine went back to the factory mid 2014 because Just Right Carbine announced they had some updates available to help solve issues with Failure To Eject, etc.  I sent the carbine back and the manufacturer installed the updated (slightly longer) buffer tube and buttstock.  While there, Manufacturer replaced Bolt & Extension, Firing Pin/Spring/Retainer, Feed Ramp, Extractor, Buffer/Buffer Spring, and Barrel.  The Third Photos shows the information that returned with the Carbine in July 2014.  So this carbine is like new and ready to rock.  

Stock Carbine comes with threaded barrel end that is capped off.  I still have the original cap but have installed a tactical tip flash hider.  I've also swapped out the stock hard plastic pistol grip with a Hogue Rubber pistol grip.  

Carbine is free floating barrel and has full length picatinney rail along the top of the rifle. Forward Guard has picatinney rail on all four sides so there is plenty of room for the goodies of your choosing.  

I have a set of Magpul Flip Up sights that will go with this gun.  I have a nothing fancy Plastic Hard Case that I will send with the gun.  I made it from a Benelli Shotgun Case, installed foam and lined the case with black material.  Nothing Fancy... but will protect gun from scratches and wondering eyes.  

Asking price is $750.  Trade interests would be Scandium Frame S&W Revolvers in .357 Magnum, 44 Magnum, and possibly .38 Special.    Possibly Glocks (no .45GAP's). title: For Sale:  Practically NEW Kahr CW380 with many extras!
postcontent:
I am selling a MINT (nearly brand new) condition Kahr CW380. This gun has had a total of approximately 300 rounds shot with it. 200 for the initial recommended "break in period" as Kahr states with all their guns then 2 trips to the range for some brief shooting. This gun is FLAWLESS condition with no scratches and has been cleaned religiously, before the first time shooting it and after the total of 3 times to the range. I have always been into Glock's then but switched my main carry pieces to Kahr's because of how slim they being a single stack but having Glock like reliability. I have owned a Kahr PM9 for years which I love and I bought this gun as a pure impulse buy. I have had a Ruger LCP before but got rid of it because it felt just to cheap and always wanted a Kahr P380 to match my PM9 HOWEVER I just couldn't find the reasoning behind spending AT LEAST $550-600 for a P380. I saw this at my local gun shop as they were unloading it from a new gun shipment. The gun looks IDENTICAL to a P380 with just a few minor insignificant differences (listed below) which lower the price of this gun to a VERY reasonable no brainer buy in my opinion. The fact it is probably the most solid built 380 WITH TRUE SIGHTS yet still is light as a feather. Overall considering its quality of build, reliability, ability to shoot +P ammo straight from Kahr's website vs. other cheaply built 380' which cannot fire +p or certain types of ammo for that matter also, super tiny, and overall a beautiful gun.

This is the only 380 I own so I am looking to part with everything 380 related along or that is specific for this gun which includes:

- Orignal Kahr box with ALL paper working including registration card, manual, Kahr info, and trigger lock.

- Orignial receipt showing the date I purchased the gun which was March 16 this year.

- A "Crossbreed" Super Tuck holster only holster custom made for a CW380 with upgraded leather horsehide for better durability. I did cut a small piece of the leather near the grip of the gun so it could be drawn easier. With tax and shipping the holster was near $100 itself. Google "Cross Breed" holsters to see prices and amazing reviews if you have never heard of them.

- "Talon rubberized heat shrink grip" which I put on all my guns to help draw and hold especially these smaller guns. It applies like a very very adhesive template that wraps around the entire grip on both sides also the front and back in which you use a heat gun or hairdryer to shrink and securely firmly wrap around the guns grip. It is as thin as paper and if you do not like you can simply peel it off with no permanet markings or indication it was ever installed new was around $20.

- De Santis "inside the pocket holster" in MINT condition. Great for summer shorts or just throwing in your front pocket as this is truly a "Pocket Sized Pistol" new was $24.

- Pack of 380 "snap caps" so you can dry fire your gun without any worries or use for training randomly loading one snap cap into your mag at the range to train how to quickly eject a jammed bullet the pack new $19.

- I have roughly half a box of some 380 FMJ target ammo along with a full box if not missing a few rounds of "Federal 90 grain Hydra-Shock Self Defense" bullets with cost $25 brand new.

- Depending on your interest I also have a fairly newly condition rarely worn (5-11 Tactical) true black leather gun belt with stainless steel buckle with no "wrinkles" or wear spots. I believe it is 36-38 inches which I will try to find the receipt or just measure but it was over $65 new and only worn slightly when I had to dress up and honestly I just prefer nylon type gun belts.

Here is how Kahr was able to offer a nearly identical gun as the P380 yet for a nearly $200-250 less which as you'll notice not many truly CRITICAL features:

"The CW380 savings come from switching out the P380’s match-grade polygonal rifled barrel for one with standard rifling, a fixed polymer front sight (driftable steel on the P380), less machining on the slide, simpler roll markings, a metal-injection-molded slide stop lever, and the inclusion of only a single 6-round magazine (the P380 comes with three)."

I am looking to get rid of EVERYTHING ask mentioned. The gun brand new cost me $359 plus taxes. All the extras I am throwing in total to minimum $250. With the flawless condition and super low use of this gun I think $250 would be a steal. The gun and everything mentioned for total of $325 would be very fair. If you have any questions or would like to see more pictures don't hesitate to call or email. REDACTED.

If you possess a firearm, you can take it to this course. Also have 50 rounds of ammunition. Upon registration, I will email you a list of items for the course. If you do not own a handgun, no worries. For $20 you can rent a 9mm for this class. But you must supply 50 rounds of 9mm luger ammo.
Learning objectives:
Safely explain and demonstrate proper gun handling, barrel awareness, knowledge, skills and attitude of having a firearm.

Examples of topics we will discuss:
-NRA motto/History
-Different kinds of handguns; revolver, semi auto and calibers
-Anatomy of bullets and caliber descriptions
-Characteristics; frames, calibers, grips and accessories
-Storage

This entry level course focuses on handgun safety and the foundational skills necessary to be safe and successful with a handgun. This firing course is objective based which uses common sense, analogical teaching methods and the students natural attributes. At the completion of this course, the student will have "developed the Knowledge, Skills and Attitude to safety and effectively handle and fire a handgun".
Upon completion of the class, the student will be presented a NRA Basic Pistol Certification recognized by ME and *NH for obtaining a Conceal Carry permit.
I will have on hand, several ME and NH Conceal Carry Permit Applications.
